---

<DocsLayout title="Copy/Paste - PrismChart - Docs" sidebar={sidebar} toc={toc} issuesUrl="https://github.com/ether-strannik/PrismChart/issues">
	<style>
		h1 {
			font-size: 1.8rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		.tagline {
			color: #666;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
			padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
		}

		p {
			color: #333;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		.section-intro {
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #000;
			margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		}

		ul {
			padding-left: 1.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		}

		li {
			padding: 0.3rem 0;
			color: #333;
		}

		code {
			background: #f5f5f5;
			padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
			border-radius: 3px;
			font-size: 0.9em;
		}

		.video-container {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
			border-radius: 8px;
			overflow: hidden;
		}

		.video-container iframe {
			display: block;
			width: 100%;
			aspect-ratio: 16/9;
			border: none;
		}
	</style>

	<h1>Copy/Paste</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Move drawings between charts and MT5 instances</p>

	<div class="video-container" id="video">
		<div id="yt-player"></div>
	</div>

	<script>
		const tag = document.createElement('script');
		tag.src = 'https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api';
		document.head.appendChild(tag);

		window.onYouTubeIframeAPIReady = function() {
			new YT.Player('yt-player', {
				videoId: 'VIDEO_ID_HERE',
				playerVars: { rel: 0, modestbranding: 1 },
				events: {
					onReady: function(e) { e.target.setPlaybackQuality('hd720'); }
				}
			});
		};
	</script>

	<h2 id="cross-chart-copy">Cross-Chart Copy</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Share drawings anywhere via clipboard.</p>
	<p>PrismChart uses the Windows clipboard to copy drawings, so you can paste them on any chart - same terminal, different terminal, even a different MT5 instance entirely.</p>
	<p>Copy captures everything: object properties, colors, styles, and sublayer relationships. Complex objects like Position Tools copy as complete units with all their components intact.</p>

	<h2 id="shortcuts">Shortcuts</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Three ways to paste.</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Ctrl+Shift+C</strong> - Copy selected objects with all properties and sublayers</li>
		<li><strong>Ctrl+Shift+V</strong> - Paste in place at original coordinates</li>
		<li><strong>Ctrl+Shift+B</strong> - Paste at click position with offset from original</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Paste in place is useful when copying analysis between charts of the same symbol. Paste at click lets you reposition the drawing relative to where you click.</p>
</DocsLayout>
